===Etymology 2===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|sco|waffle||to waver, flutter}}, a variation of the {{m|sco|waff||to flutter, wave}}, related to {{cog|en|wave}}, with the suffix {{cog|sco|-le}} added. Alternatively, perhaps derived from {{m|en|waff}}, an imitation of a dog's yelp (cf. {{m|en|woof}}). Also note {{cog|ang|wæflian||to talk foolishly}}.

